"Why, indeed? You seem most fortunate in having an employee who comes under the full market price.
It is not a common experience among employers in this age. I don't know that your assistant is not
as remarkable as your advertisement."

"Oh, he has his faults, too," said Mr. Wilson. "Never was such a fellow for photography. Snapping
away with a camera when he ought to be improving his mind, and then diving down into the cellar like
a rabbit into its hole to develop his pictures. That is his main fault, but on the whole he's a good
worker. There's no vice in him."